bilingual.source: We can help you develop new skills step by step.
bilingual.target: 我们可以一步步帮助你发展新技能。

bilingual.source: We do not know how circuses will develop in the future.

bilingual.source: Make a flow chart to show how the play will develop and then finish.

bilingual.source: Can you tell me what I should do if I want to develop new skills?

bilingual.source: Podcasting is an excellent way to develop your speaking and computer skills.
bilingual.target: 播客是发展你的口语和计算机技能的好方法。

我们需要发展新的技术。

bilingual.source: She wants to develop her skills in painting.

bilingual.source: This relationship could develop into a marriage.

list.abstract: develop（ [dɪˈveləp]），英语单词，作动词用，为成长；发育；发展。短语搭配有develop into（发展成为），例句为“Develop broad, general knowledge and experience.（发展广泛的、大众的知识和经验）”。 develop及物动词类近义词有exploit、open up，不及物动词类近义词有grow、flower，名词形式为development、developer。

yingyinNormal.en: Along with our allies, we will support the people of Ukraine as they develop their democracy and economy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 与我们的盟国一起，我们将支持乌克兰人民发展他们的民主和经济。

yingyinNormal.en: And that led us to propose and develop this very specialized experiment, which one of my colleagues referred to gleefully as a wild-goose chase.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这引导我们提出并发展这个非常专业的实验，我的一位同事高兴地称作野鹅追逐。

yingyinNormal.en: I think we need to encourage foreign investment and develop new forms of economic growth rather than make one of the world's poorest countries even poorer.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我认为我们应该鼓励外国资本进入发展新的经济增长模式，而不是让刚果一穷到底。

yingyinNormal.en: What you choose to do with these principles is up to you. You have to be an independent thinker, because only you can develop your own principles based on your own values.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你要自己选择怎么看待这些法则。要有独立思考的能力，因为只有你能基于自己的价值观发展自己的法则。

yingyinNormal.en: Because I could see these events transpire in pretty much the same ways over and over, I could more clearly see the cause-effect relationships that govern their behaviors, which allowed me to develop better principles that I could express in both words and algorithms.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为我可以看到这些事件以同样的方式重复发生，所以可以更清楚的看到他们行为的因果关系，使我能够发展出更好的法则，既能用话语也能用算法表达。

yingyinNormal.en: You can't develop a problem that fast.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你哪有可能这么快就染上瘾。

yingyinNormal.en: And develop an insane Pilates habit, and buy a dog, or a horse, and develop a crush on your riding instructor.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然后逐渐养成疯狂做普拉提的习惯，买条狗或一匹马，然后看上了骑术教练。

yingyinNormal.en: So you all have the power in your own way to develop your own Angel Network.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因此，你们每个人都有能力打造自己的天使网络项目。

yingyinNormal.en: If this occurs, then there's a greater chance they'll develop into cancer cells.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果这种情况发生，它们就会有很大的几率演变成癌症细胞。

yingyinNormal.en: It takes years to develop one's flexibility! And years longer to apply it in combat!
yingyinNormal.zh: 韧性与柔性要花数年的功夫，能活用在对阵中又得数年。

yingyinNormal.en: Such as external planet and the planet likely to develop life N=R*Fp*Ne*Fl*Fi*Fc*L. Yeah, that one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 比如具有行星的星系或者有生命存在的行星N=R*Fp*Ne*Fl*Fi*Fc*L。对，就是那个。

yingyinNormal.en: And the key to life is to develop an internal moral emotional GPS that can tell you which way to go.
yingyinNormal.zh: 命运的关键在于培育出一个内在的道德情感导航仪，使其能够为你指明方向。

yingyinNormal.en: I was going to ask them: which scientist both helped to develop calculus and had a famous cookie named after him?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我本来打算问他们，哪个科学家既对微积分有贡献又有一款饼干以他命名？

yingyinNormal.en: Assuming you'd be able to get the parts, and develop the engineering skills to assemble them, which I don't see as likely. Hacha!
yingyinNormal.zh: 前提是你能找齐零件并拥有足够的工程技术能把自己组装成好丈夫，不过应该是没戏吧，好笑吧！

yingyinNormal.en: I see no large upcoming expenditures unless they develop an affordable technology to fuse my skeleton with Adamantium like Wolverine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我最近没有什么大的开销，除非他们发明了新的科技能将我的骨骼铸成金刚狼一样的艾德曼合金。

yingyinNormal.en: The pesticide industry has had to develop this wide-ranging chemical arsenal because the insects have their own secret weapon, evolution.
yingyinNormal.zh: 杀虫剂产业必须发明各式各样的化学武器，因为昆虫也有它们的秘密武器，进化。

yingyinNormal.en: While we all have the gene, such as BRCA1, that can cause cancer, it's only when these genes fail at their function that problems develop.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们每个人身体里都有诸如乳腺癌1号基因这类可能导致癌症的基因存在，但癌症只会发生在这些基因失效时。

yingyinNormal.en: While we develop a system to help you determine how much intelligence to act on which attacks to stop, which to let through. Statistical analysis.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在形成的系统下就能帮你分析情报，部署进攻停止或是放弃。数据分析。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, I've taken the liberty of drafting these workflow charts which outline our various duties and the path we will follow as we develop our ground-breaking new app.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，我已经自作主张起草了这些工作流程图，这里列出了我们形形色色的职务，以及开发这独创程序过程中需遵照的事项。

yingyinNormal.en: Leonard, I was... What's Kripke doing here? Oh, he's just helping us develop a better, more efficient neutrino comm system that we're gonna pitch to the military, making yours obsolete.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莱纳德，我... 克里普奇在这里干什么？他正在帮我们开发一种更好，更高效的中微子通讯系统我们就能联系军队，彻底打垮你。

examination_example.sentence: It is not enough to say that the algorithms DeepMind <highlight>develops</highlight> will benefit patients and save lives.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 仅仅说DeepMind开发的算法将造福患者并挽救生命是不够的。

examination_example.sentence: For instance, one of the apps the students are <highlight>developing</highlight> suggests movies based on your mood.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，学生们正在开发的一款应用程序可以根据你的情绪推荐电影。

examination_example.sentence: That should create more collaborative endeavors and help to <highlight>develop</highlight> projects aimed directly at solving global problems.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这将产生更多的合作努力，并有助于开发旨在直接解决全球问题的项目。

examination_example.sentence: These demands resulted in a very rapid expansion of the systems of higher education, <highlight>developing</highlight> very rapidly in the 1970s and 1980s.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些需求导致了高等教育体系的迅速扩张，在20世纪70年代和80年代迅速发展。

examination_example.sentence: What made photography <highlight>develop</highlight> slowly in the Victorian period?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 是什么使摄影在维多利亚时期发展缓慢?

examination_example.sentence: The prevention of this type of fraud is no easy task, and a new field of computer science is <highlight>developing</highlight> to cope with security issues.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 防止这类欺诈并非易事，而计算机科学正在发展一个新的领域来应对安全问题。

examination_example.sentence: For example, heavier women are less likely to <highlight>develop</highlight> calcium deficiency than thin women.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，较胖的女性比较瘦的女性患钙缺乏的可能性较小。

examination_example.sentence: By <highlight>developing</highlight> a culture of responsibility, repair, and reuse, you can build customer loyalty based on shared values and responsibilities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 通过发展一种责任、维修和再利用的文化，你可以在共同的价值观和责任感的基础上建立客户忠诚度。

examination_example.sentence: Other math educators say what's needed is to help students <highlight>develop</highlight> a better relationship with math earlier, rather than teaching them less math altogether.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其他数学教育工作者表示，需要帮助学生更早地与数学建立更好的关系，而不是完全不教他们数学。

examination_example.sentence: The results highlight the need to <highlight>develop</highlight> effective early interventions to help those with attention problems stay on track academically.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些结果突显了形成有效的早期干预措施的必要性，以帮助那些有注意力问题的人在学业上保持在正轨上。

examination_example.sentence: As an integral part of learning, it brings about positive changes, making people <highlight>develop</highlight> and grow.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作为学习的一个组成部分，它引起了积极的变化，使人发展和成长。

examination_example.sentence: The books we share with young children can be a valuable opportunity to <highlight>develop</highlight> children's understanding of themselves and others.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们和孩子们分享书籍是一个宝贵机会，能够培养孩子对自己和他人的理解。

examination_example.sentence: This can help <highlight>develop</highlight> understanding, acceptance and appreciation of diversity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这有助于培养对多样性的理解、接受和欣赏。

examination_example.sentence: The study included 386 kindergarteners, a multi-site clinical trial in the U.S. that in 1991 began tracking how children <highlight>developed</highlight> across their lives.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这项研究包括386名幼儿园教师，这是美国的一项多点临床试验项目，于1991年开始跟踪儿童在一生中的发育情况。

examination_example.sentence: Designer sportswear was not modeled on that of Europe, as "modern art" would later be; it was genuinely invented and <highlight>developed</highlight> in America.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 设计师运动服并非模仿欧洲的，而是后来的“现代艺术”。 它是在美国真正发明和发展的。

sense_info_list.en: construct or convert a building so as to improve existing resources

examination_example.sentence: A novel type of steel has been <highlight>developed</highlight> that resists fractures at much lower temperatures.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一种可在更低的温度下抗断裂的新型钢被开发出来了。

examination_example.sentence: They <highlight>developed</highlight> a complex mechanical process involving repeated heating and very severe mechanical deformation, known as temp forming.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们开发了一套复杂的机械工艺，包括反复加热和非常严重的机械变形，称之为临时成形。

examination_example.sentence: Toyohashi University of Technology has <highlight>developed</highlight> Terapio, a robotic medical cart that can make hospital rounds, deliver medications and other items, and retrieve records.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 丰桥技术科学大学(Toyohashi University of Technology)开发了一种机器人医疗车“Terapio”，它可以在医院巡视，运送药品和其他物品，并检索记录。

examination_example.sentence: Scientists have proven that despite their poorly <highlight>developed</highlight> small eyes, these bats still can see during the day.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 科学家们已经证明，尽管它们的小眼睛发育不良，这些蝙蝠仍然可以在白天看到东西。

examination_example.sentence: Tthe Eskimos of Greenland have <highlight>developed</highlight> certain genetic adaptations that help them digest and utilize this fat-rich diet.

develop的现在分词developing意为“发展中的”，其过去分词developed意为“发达的”：
The United States is a highly developed country while the Democratic People's Republic of Korea is a developing one.

examination_example.sentence: In 1980, Iceland started to <highlight>develop</highlight> its tourist industry.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 1980年，冰岛开始发展旅游业。

examination_example.sentence: They are not able to <highlight>develop</highlight> the same social skills as children from big families.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们无法像来自大家庭的孩子那样发展社交技能。

examination_example.sentence: How fast China is <highlight>developing</highlight>!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 中国发展得多快啊！

sense_info_list.en: start to exist, experience, or possess

examination_example.sentence: While she was in Milan, she <highlight>developed</highlight> a taste for fine art.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在米兰期间，她对美术产生了浓厚的兴趣。

examination_example.sentence: I also <highlight>developed</highlight> a new hobby—I planted a pot (盆) of flowers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我还培养了一个新的爱好——我种了一盆的花。

examination_example.sentence: There is nothing easier than <highlight>developing</highlight> good habits.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 没有什么比养成好习惯更容易的了。

sense_info_list.zh: 开发; 研制; 制定

examination_example.sentence: Yuan Longping, a great scientist, is the first person to <highlight>develop</highlight> a kind of hybrid rice (杂交水稻) which helps fight hunger in China.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 袁隆平，一位伟大的科学家，是第一位研制出杂交水稻，帮助中国对抗饥饿的人。

examination_example.sentence: She <highlight>developed</highlight> an app to help them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她开发了一个应用程序来帮助他们。

examination_example.sentence: Governments around the world have <highlight>developed</highlight> laws to stop this.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 世界各国政府都已制定了法律来制止这种情况。

sense_info_list.en: to begin to have something such as a disease or a problem

examination_example.sentence: Not only that, he <highlight>developed</highlight> a serious illness and became blind.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不仅如此，他还得了重病，失明了。

examination_example.sentence: His mother <highlight>developed</highlight> mental health problems.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他的母亲出现了精神健康问题。

examination_example.sentence: During these years, the body <highlight>develops</highlight> in many ways.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在这些年里，身体各方面都在发育。

sense_info_list.en: make an idea, a story, etc. clearer by explaining it further

examination_example.sentence: How does the writer <highlight>develop</highlight> Paragraph 5?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作者是如何展开第5段的？

sense_info_list.en: to treat film which has been used to take photographs with chemicals so that the pictures can be seen

examination_example.sentence: We hand in a roll of film, it gets <highlight>developed</highlight>, and we choose one photo for the competition.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们交上一卷胶卷，冲洗后，我们选择一张照片参加比赛。
